              <abstract>
                <p><italic>Bacillus cereus</italic> strain LCT-BC25, which was carried by the Shenzhou VIII spacecraft, traveled in space for about 398 h. To investigate the response of <italic>B. cereus</italic> to space environments, we determined the genome sequence of <italic>B. cereus</italic> strain LCT-BC25, which was isolated after space flight.</p>
